page.title: 02WOODS
page.content: The{Goldings}wood in Hertford Heath is deciduous.We found Beech,Hazel,Conker, Oak and Silver Birch trees.Bushes were Holly,Hawthorn,and Broom.The flowers were Bluebells,wood sorrel, Wild Rose, Cranes Bill,Goosegrass,Vetch ,Delphinium elatum,Bracken Peziza repanda,White fork moss,woodland anemone,by,Marsh Horsetails and Hump Agrimoney.{ {Balls Wood}is Forestry Comission land. It is similar to{Goldings,}but,it had streams and pheasants. {Morgans Walk}in Hertford is deciduous.The are the same as{Goldings {Wood.}Flowers were Cowparsley,Rosebay, Willowherb,smooth fruited cornsalad.
